                            </h4>
											<div id="tab-2" class="panel-collapse collapse">
												<p>
VAT applies equally on tax-registered businesses managed on the UAE mainland and in the free zones. However, if the UAE Cabinet defines a certain free zone as a ‘designated zone’, it must be treated as outside the UAE for tax purposes. The transfer of goods between designated zones are tax-free.												</p>
											</div>
